---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/information-page.scss";
---

<BaseLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Accessibility | IzignaMx"
  description="Accessibility commitment, keyboard support, and equivalent content for the IzignaMx Capability Book."
  canonicalPath="/en/accessibility/"
  alternatePath="/es/accesibilidad/"
>
  <article class="information-page" data-pagefind-body>
    <header class="information-page__header">
      <p class="information-page__eyebrow">Barrier-free access</p>
      <h1>Accessibility by design.</h1>
      <p class="information-page__intro">
        We target WCAG 2.2 Level AA and a useful experience when animation, canvas, or JavaScript
        is unavailable.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="information-page__sections">
      <section aria-labelledby="motion-title">
        <h2 id="motion-title">Motion under your control</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            Explore checks <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>, data-saving preferences, and device
            capabilities before creating a canvas. When the advanced experience is available, the
            persistent “Reduce advanced motion” control immediately replaces it with its static
            composition.
          </p>
          <p>
            “Restore advanced motion” recomputes the device policy; it never overrides a system
            constraint. Motion level never changes the available content, evidence, or ability to
            complete a task.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="canvas-title">
        <h2 id="canvas-title">Canvas alternative</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            Projects, capabilities, relationships, and calls to action remain available as semantic
            HTML. Fallback images have stable dimensions and contextual alternative text.
          </p>
          <p>
            If a visual scene fails or is disabled, static navigation preserves the same
            information and destinations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="keyboard-title">
        <h2 id="keyboard-title">Keyboard and focus</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <ul>
            <li>The “Skip to content” link appears when focused.</li>
            <li>Controls and links support keyboard navigation and visible focus.</li>
            <li>Forms use labels, native validation, and announceable messages.</li>
            <li>Interactions do not depend only on hover, dragging, or color.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="feedback-title">
        <h2 id="feedback-title">Report a barrier</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            If you encounter a barrier, email
            <a href="mailto:hola@izignamx.com?subject=Capability%20Book%20accessibility">hola@izignamx.com</a>.
            Include the URL, browser or assistive technology, and a description of the issue;
            avoid unnecessary personal information.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
